// p70 — `from X use { y as local }` import aliases (v3.11.0).
//
// Until v3.11.0 the parser rejected `as` inside a `from X use { ... }`
// block (`Expected '}' (found 'as')`), even though every other piece
// of the toolchain — LSP scanImports, runtime resolver, the
// whole-module `from X as alias` form — already understood the
// concept. This release closes that gap.
//
// The classic motivating case: two same-named exports from sibling
// stdlib packages. `url` and `toml` both export `parse(String)`; without
// aliases the second `from url use { parse }` collides with the first
// `from toml use { parse }` in the same file. With aliases each lands
// under a distinct local name and dispatches to the right module.
//
// Sema records each alias in the module's VisibilityContext.importAliases
// map; `lookupTopLevel` checks that map first and dereferences the local
// name to the source name before the rest of the resolution chain runs.
// The chosen FunctionNode carries its canonical linkage name, which
// Codegen reads via the same `CallNode::resolvedLinkageName` slot v3.6.0
// added for cross-package overload disambiguation.

from url use { parse as url_parse, URL }
from toml use { parse as toml_parse }

u: URL := url_parse("https://example.com/path?q=1")
print(u.host)    // = example.com
print(u.scheme)  // = https

m: Map := toml_parse("k = 1\nname = \"q\"")
print(m.get("k"))     // = 1
print(m.get("name"))  // = q
